This solution uses a depth-first search (DFS) approach to find the smallest subtree containing all the deepest nodes. The `dfs` function returns a tuple containing the node that is the root of the smallest subtree with all the deepest nodes and the depth of those nodes. By comparing the depths of the left and right subtrees, the function determines which subtree contains all the deepest nodes or if the current node is the smallest subtree containing all the deepest nodes.
